ance goals, have been met.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"result\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:47:53.985Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"stats\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"total_tokens\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":820285,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"input_tokens\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":815255,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"output_tokens\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":1757,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cached\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":503583,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"input\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":311672,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"duration_ms\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":58994,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_calls\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":16,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"models\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"gemini-3-flash-preview\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"total_tokens\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":820285,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"input_tokens\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":815255,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"output_tokens\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":1757,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cached\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":503583,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"input\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":311672}}}}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++YOLO mode is enabled. All tool calls will be automatically approved.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++YOLO mode is enabled. All tool calls will be automatically approved.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+diff --git a/sdp/verification/t-019 @20260425t183959z-verify.md b/sdp/verification/t-019 @20260425t183959z-verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+new file mode 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+index 0000000..51e8839\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+--- /dev/null\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++++ b/sdp/verification/t-019 @20260425t183959z-verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++# Verification Report — T-019 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260425T183959Z_1777164786.log\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Date:** 2026-04-26\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++**Artifacts Reviewed:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/harmonic_planner.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- `ESCALATIONS.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Correctness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++The implementation of `transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> int` correctly computes the smallest semitone offset required to align a sample's detected pitch with the nearest in-key pitch class. It handles the octave wrap correctly by searching in both directions. The tie-breaking logic favors negative transposition, which is consistent and verified by tests.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++All acceptance criteria are met:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Transposition maps `pitch_hz` to the nearest in-key pitch using the artist's B-rooted palette.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Samples with `pitch_confidence < 0.4` or `pitch_hz <= 0` return 0 semitones, correctly playing \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"atonally\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- Tests cover known pitch/key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and octave wrap shortest-path selection.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++The implementation leverages `harmonic_planner.py` for canonical key normalization and scale definitions, ensuring consistency with the rest of the SenseWeave harmony engine. The coding style and test patterns match the existing codebase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++No security vulnerabilities were identified. The implementation uses standard math libraries and does not involve unsafe operations or credential handling.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++The code is concise, well-documented, and follows idiomatic Python patterns. The tests are comprehensive and use appropriate fixtures (standard within the project). Mandatory hardening checks regarding `bootstrap_identity` were found to be already addressed in the daemon startup flows (`daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py`).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++- [x] (Minor/Environmental) `pytest tests/ -x` encountered a `PermissionError` in `test_daemon_fallback.py` due to macOS Seatbelt restrictions on `~/.promptclaw/pets.json`. This is an environmental constraint unrelated to the T-019 changes. Focused tests for the new implementation (`tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py`) passed successfully.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++The implementation is solid and integrates well with the established harmonic planning utilities. No further actions required for this task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+diff --git a/tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py b/tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+index fb58db4..264193b 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+--- a/tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++++ b/tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+@@ -15,6 +15,7 @@ from senseweave.sampler_dispatch import (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+     FX_PRESETS_BY_MODE,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+     SamplerDispatcher,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+     SamplerHandle,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    transpose_to_key,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+@@ -321,3 +322,51 @@ def test_play_sampler_forwards_fx_preset(tmp_path: Path) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+     addresses = [call[0] for call in osc.calls]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+     assert addresses == [\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/b_alloc\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/b_allocRead\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/n_set\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/s_new\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++class _PitchedRecord:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    def __init__(self, pitch_hz: float, pitch_confidence: float = 0.9) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++        self.pitch_hz = pitch_hz\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++        self.pitch_confidence = pitch_confidence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++def test_transpose_to_key_in_key_pitch_returns_zero() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    # B aeolian = B C# D E F# G A; A4 (440 Hz) is in scale.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    assert transpose_to_key(_PitchedRecord(440.0), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Bm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") == 0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++def test_transpose_to_key_picks_nearest_in_key_pitch() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    # B aeolian pitch classes: {11, 1, 2, 4, 6, 7, 9}. C5 (~523.25) is pc 0;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    # nearest in-key is B (pc 11), one semitone down.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    assert transpose_to_key(_PitchedRecord(523.25), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Bm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") == -1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++def test_transpose_to_key_octave_wrap_prefers_short_path() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    # C5 in B major scale {11, 1, 3, 4, 6, 8, 10}: B is one semitone down (-1)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    # via wrap, not 11 semitones up. Verifies wrap handling.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    assert transpose_to_key(_PitchedRecord(523.25), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"B\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") == -1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++def test_transpose_to_key_low_confidence_returns_zero() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    # Out-of-key pitch but low confidence — atonal texture, no transposition.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    assert transpose_to_key(_PitchedRecord(523.25, pitch_confidence=0.39), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Bm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") == 0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++def test_transpose_to_key_confidence_at_threshold_transposes() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    # Confidence exactly 0.4 still transposes (>= floor).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    assert transpose_to_key(_PitchedRecord(523.25, pitch_confidence=0.4), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Bm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") == -1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++def test_transpose_to_key_zero_pitch_returns_zero() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    assert transpose_to_key(_PitchedRecord(0.0, pitch_confidence=1.0), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Bm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") == 0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++def test_transpose_to_key_c_major_known_combination() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    # C# (~277.18) → C major scale {0,2,4,5,7,9,11}: nearest is C (-1) or D (+1);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    # algorithm prefers the negative direction on ties.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    assert transpose_to_key(_PitchedRecord(277.18), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"C\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") == -1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++def test_transpose_to_key_handles_higher_octave() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    # A6 (1760 Hz) in B aeolian — A is in scale, no transposition.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n++    assert transpose_to_key(_PitchedRecord(1760.0), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Bm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") == 0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+codex\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+I confirmed the feature and tests are already in the last three commits; next I’m validating