ch_sample` core<br/>- tests verify both lifecycles and that they can run concurrently without buffer-id collision |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 5 | T-005 | Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-014 | — | - `master_bus.apply_master_bus_scene` recognizes a `sampler_bus` mix slot with default gain -3 dB (peak-normalized so quieter library samples don't disappear)<br/>- post-mix compression for the sampler slot has `compression_ratio = 1.5` (lower than the 4.0 used elsewhere) so grain transients survive<br/>- tests verify gain staging on a known-amplitude input and grain-transient preservation via peak-vs-RMS ratio |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 6 | T-006 | Implement `sample_capture_daemon.py` rolling 60-second buffers reading from `system:capture_1` (contact mic) and `system:capture_2` (room mic) via JACK. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-015 | — | - daemon opens two JACK ports `cypherclaw-capture:in_contact` and `cypherclaw-capture:in_room`<br/>- each maintains a 60-second numpy ring buffer at 48 kHz<br/>- exposes `get_window(source, duration_sec, offset_sec) -> np.ndarray` for the moment-detector to pull recent windows<br/>- handles JACK xruns gracefully (logs, does not crash)<br/>- tests with a synthetic JACK input fixture verify ring-buffer correctness, window extraction, and xrun recovery |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 7 | T-007 | Implement interesting-moment detector: novelty (spectral flux) + transient density + RMS thresholds + duration-min/max gating. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCS-016 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::InterestingMomentDetector` pulls 1-second windows every 250 ms<br/>- flags a window when: `spectral_flux > 0.6 * recent_median` AND `rms > -45 dBFS` AND `transient_count >= 2` AND `since_last_capture > 30 sec`<br/>- on flag, expands to a 4–8 second window centered on the flagged sub-window (length proportional to spectral richness)<br/>- thresholds are tunable via env / config<br/>- tests with canned audio fixtures (silence, footsteps, dishwasher hum, music) verify expected flag/no-flag for each |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 8 | T-008 | Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCS-017 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::auto_tag(window, context) -> dict` returns a dict mergeable into `SampleRecord`<br/>- arc_phase / mood / presence pulled from `/tmp/organism_state.json` and `/tmp/room_presence.json`<br/>- character tags derived from heuristics: spectral_centroid<800Hz → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"; narrow-band high-centroid → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"metallic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"; sustained_amplitude_ratio>0.7 → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sustained\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"; transient_density>3/sec → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"percussive\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"; pitch_confidence>0.7 → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"harmonic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"; etc.<br/>- tests verify each heuristic against canned fixtures and that the merged record validates against `SampleRecord` schema |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 9 | T-009 | Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-018 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::save_capture(window, source, tags) -> SampleRecord` writes WAV with filename pattern `<source>_<YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ>_<arc>_<sampleid>.wav`<br/>- WAV is 24-bit PCM, 48 kHz, peak-normalized to -1 dBFS unless `peak < -30 dBFS` in which case raw is preserved<br/>- record inserted into `index.sqlite` with `gain_db` set to the normalization adjustment<br/>- tests verify file presence, format (24/48), peak-normalize behavior, and DB row |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 10 | T-010 | Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-019 | — | - `tools/duet_composer.py` post-song hook calls `sample_capture_daemon::self_quote(score_summary)` when arc_payoff > 0.6 AND click_count == 0 AND mode != working_ambience<br/>- daemon captures from `SuperCollider:out_1` (via `system:capture_X` after a small JACK loopback connection it manages itself) the 4-second window centered on the moment of peak rolling_peak during the song<br/>- saves to `samples/self/` with `arc_phase`, `mood`, `mode`, and a `self_quote_source_song_id` extra tag<br/>- tests with a mock self-listener stream and arc-payoff fixture verify trigger condition, capture window, and tag propagation |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n **Sprint 1 total:** ~30 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -29,16 +29,11 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 11 | T-011 | Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-030 | T-001 | - `render/rules/sensor_intent.py` takes raw SenseWeave sensor stream, applies one-pole IIR smoothing (α≈0.1), threshold with hysteresis, and multiplies by sensor→intention weight matrix<br/>- outputs aggregate_intentions, never direct synth parameters<br/>- listener-reverse-engineer test: given recorded sensor stream and rendered output, no single sensor can be shown to drive any single synth parameter at correlation > 0.85 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 12 | T-012 | Implement bounded reactive delta track in scheduler with per-parameter modulation caps. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-031 | T-001 | - scheduler writes sensor_tempo_scale ∈ [0.92, 1.08], sensor_amp_scale ∈ [0.80, 1.20], sensor_brightness ∈ [-1.0, +1.0] onto each Event<br/>- delta track is persisted as JSON alongside audio output for replay<br/>- out-of-bounds values clamped and logged<br/>- tests verify clamping, persistence, and replay consumes the delta track |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 13 | T-013 | Expose aggregate-intention telemetry (global_energy/restraint/brightness) in operator diagnostics, never raw one-to-one mappings. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-033 | T-001 | - `operator_diagnostics.py` extended with aggregate_intentions block<br/>- raw sensor values are NOT surfaced alongside synth parameters in diagnostics (prevents accidentally re-introducing gimmicky reverse-mappings)<br/>- tests verify telemetry shape and absence of raw pairings |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 14 | T-014 | Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-034 | T-001 | - `render/metrics.py` computes each metric on PerformedPart<br/>- tooling: partitura for score I/O, mir_eval for segmentation, MusDr/MusPy for symbolic metrics, librosa for audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty, madmom for beat/tempo cross-check<br/>- documented pass bands from the research: IOI CoV 0.04–0.12, velocity σ 12–22, D