nt, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar presence, schema, and ability to replay from sidecar alone |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 11 | T-011 | Implement anti-pattern detectors: `sampler_dominating` (sampler event count > 0.6 × total events) and `sampler_silent_quintet_member` (sampler used in <5% of last 50 pieces, mode-weighted). | T1 | 7 | 3 | CCS-030 | T-001 | - integrated into `render/antipatterns.py` (CCH-015)<br/>- `sampler_dominating` fires per-piece, surfaces in metrics gate as warning (downgrade to MUST FIX after 3 consecutive)<br/>- `sampler_silent_quintet_member` fires across rolling window of last 50 pieces; mode-weighted means the threshold scales with `sampler_density` per mode (so working_ambience never trips it)<br/>- tests verify each detector with synthetic piece histories |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 12 | T-012 | End-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw: capture a known room sound, watch the composer self-quote it within 3 pieces, verify the self-listener observes the resulting peaks. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-031 | T-001 | - `my-claw/tests/test_sampler_e2e.py` (skipped on CI, runs on cypherclaw via `pytest -m cypherclaw_e2e`)<br/>- plays a 4-second sine sweep through the speakers, lets contact/room mic capture it, waits for the daemon to detect+tag, forces the composer to compose 3 short pieces, asserts at least one of them dispatched a sampler with the captured sample<br/>- self-listener observes nonzero peak in the expected scene<br/>- documented in `docs/sampler-smoke-test.md` |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 13 | T-013 | Update `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to reflect the quintet, document the sampler architecture in `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md`, and add a one-page artistic-intent