sdp/verification/t-019@20260427t001208zd-verify.md:55:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-27T19:01:04.733Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777316464733_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-019 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260427T001208Zd_1777316422.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-27\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py`\n- `tests/test_usage_journal.py`\n- `tests/test_usage_journal_integration.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/daemon.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_daemon.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly defaults missing or empty `source_kind` entries in the usage journal to 'unknown' during deserialization.\n- `SamplePlay.from_dict` in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py` was updated to handle missing `source_kind` and ensure it defaults to `\"unknown\"`.\n- `_derive_source_kind` was updated to check for `source_kind` in metadata before falling back to `sample_origin`.\n- Legacy parsing is verified by `test_read_journal_legacy_entries_default_source_kind_to_unknown`.\n\n## Completeness\nThe solution addresses both the backfill requirement (missing keys) and the normalization of empty strings (falsy values) as 'unknown'.\n- `test_read_journal_treats_empty_source_kind_as_unknown` confirms that `\"\"` is also normalized to `\"unknown\"`.\n- Integration tests in `tests/test_usage_journal_integration.py` were updated to verify `source_kind` propagation through a full piece-composition lifecycle.\n\n## Consistency\nThe changes follow established patterns in the codebase for `from_dict` deserialization and metadata derivation. The new tests are consistent with existing journal verification patterns.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices were introduced. The changes are confined to JSON deserialization logic and metadata mapping.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is surgical and well-tested. All 23 tests in `tests/test_usage_journal.py` and the integration test in `tests/test_usage_journal_integration.py` pass.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [x] No issues found.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation of the `source_kind` fallback and the legacy journal-replay tests is solid. The \"Candidate Hardening\" items regarding `bootstrap_identity` were also cross-checked and found to be correctly implemented in all relevant daemon entrypoints.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-019 @20260427t001208zd-verify.md"}}
