     1	# Task frac-0008 Specification: Commission Context Depth 2
     2	
     3	## Problem Statement
     4	
     5	`my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` derives the
     6	`(day_phase, weekly_phase)` pair that the duet composer feeds into
     7	`commission_piece`. Today the module is a single trivial helper that
     8	or-chains `getattr` calls into one return. The fractal scanner therefore
     9	classifies it at depth 1 (`1/1 trivial, 0 real`): callers cannot ask the
    10	module for normalized attention/pressure values or for a stable bundle of
    11	the inputs the score-tree commission actually needs, so the same `getattr`
    12	plumbing is duplicated in `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece`.
    13	
    14	The task is to deepen the module to a simple depth-2 implementation: one
    15	straightforward path that adds typed, pure helpers for projecting the
    16	commission inputs and summarizing them while preserving the existing
    17	`commission_context_from_tracker_plan` behavior so `duet_composer` and the
    18	existing test suite keep working.
    19	
    20	## Technical Approach
    21	
    22	Extend `commission_context.py` in place with a small set of pure, typed
    23	helpers around the existing `(tracker_plan, world)` inputs:
    24	
    25	- `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` — keep its
    26	  public `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` contract but rewrite the body to walk
    27	  candidate sources in order, strip whitespace, and only fall back to the
    28	  `"day"` default for `day_phase` (weekly_phase keeps `""` when both
    29	  sources are empty, matching today's behavior).
    30	- `attention_pressure_from_world(world)` — return
    31	  `(attention_score, narrative_pressure)` pulled from `world.attention_score`
    32	  and `world.experimentation_bias`, each clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]` and
    33	  defaulting to `0.0` when the source is missing or non-numeric. This
    34	  centralizes the inline `float(world.attention_score or 0.0)` plumbing
    35	  used by `duet_composer`.
    36	- `CommissionInputs` — a frozen dataclass of the fields
    37	  `commission_piece` actually consumes: `cadence_state`, `occupancy_state`,
    38	  `day_phase`, `weekly_phase`, `attention_score`, `narrative_pressure`,
    39	  `song_num`, `hour`. Constructed via
    40	  `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world, song_num, hour)`.
    41	- `summarize_commission_context(inputs)` — return a stable diagnostic
    42	  dictionary (`cadence`, `occupancy`, `day_phase`, `weekly_phase`,
    43	  `song_num`, `hour`, `attention` bucket label, `narrative_pressure`)
    44	  so operator logs can render a snapshot without exposing dataclass
    45	  internals or runtime objects.
    46	
    47	The existing public `commission_context_from_tracker_plan` keyword-only
    48	signature and return type are preserved, so `duet_composer` and
    49	`tests/test_commission_context.py` keep working without modification. No
    50	new dependencies, migrations, secrets, provider commands, or database
    51	columns are introduced.
    52	
    53	## Edge Cases
    54	
    55	- `commission_context_from_tracker_plan` strips whitespace from candidate
    56	  values, so a tracker plan with `day_phase="  "` falls through to the
    57	  world before defaulting to `"day"`.
    58	- `commission_context_from_tracker_plan` keeps the empty-string fallback
    59	  for `weekly_phase` to preserve today's behavior (callers may pass `""`
    60	  through to `commission_piece` unchanged).
    61	- `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps non-numeric or `None` inputs to
    62	  `0.0`, swallowing `TypeError`/`ValueError` from `float()` so a stale
    63	  world snapshot cannot crash the score-tree path.
    64	- `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps values above `1.0` down to `1.0`
    65	  and values below `0.0` up to `0.0`, so unexpected sensor spikes do not
    66	  propagate raw into commission scoring.
    67	- `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan` coerces `song_num`/`hour` through
    68	  `int()` and supplies `"uncertain"` as the default occupancy label when
